The deutonymph was illustrated in the original description of the species, but not described (Figure 23 in
Karg, 2000 a
). The following characteristics are present in the original illustrations of the deutonymph, but do not agree with our observations of the paratype specimens: podonotal shield smooth and with 23 pairs of setae; opisthonotal shield reticulate; ventrianal shield smooth; with a longitudinal line extending from the anterior end of the peritreme to the level of coxa I; lyrifissures present only on the sternal shield (two pairs).
